BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-018@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:UN Tech Over Hack-A-Thon
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260622T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260622T180000
DESCRIPTION:This Hack-A-Thon will offer a space for a collaborative innovation sprint where participants use open source tools and artificial intelligence to rapidly build solutions addressing global challenges aligned with UN goals Challenge 1: Safety, Supervision, and Governance in the Agentic World Safety, Supervision and Governance in the Agentic World will be a challenge developed by AESIA (the Spanish Agency for the Supervision of Artificial Intelligence) and the Spanish Open Source AI Community, led \nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-019@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Edit-A-Thon
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260622T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260622T180000
DESCRIPTION:This event aims to leverage participants’ research, documentation and critical thinking abilities to enhance selected Wikipedia pages of relevance. Throughout the day, experts and mentors will assist participants in updating these pages so as to publish in-depth, accurate reports\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-2026-020@osweekplus.nyc
SUMMARY:Maintain-A-Thon
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260622T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260622T180000
DESCRIPTION:This event, organized for open source maintainers, stewards, and policymakers, spotlights the maintenance of critical open source infrastructure. It consists of two tracks: one featuring open source maintainer-led sessions that share knowledge and best practices and surface the craft of open source software maintenance through real-world examples; and another dedicated to institutional capacity building and long-term stewardship\nRSVP: https://www.unopensource.org/agenda
LOCATION:New York, NY
END:VEVENT
